      • constructClosure

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Boolean> constructClosure(java.util.HashSet<java.lang.String> initialState)
        This function calculates the transitive closure of the current functional dependencies given the set of initial terms that are true. It does so by iterating the dependencies and adding newly discovered terms. The construction terminates when no new terms can be derived from the current set of terms.
        Parameters:
        initialState - The set of terms that are true before the calculation of the closure
        Returns:
        A set of terms that should hold true
